## Goals
- Headless provisioning (no screen / no keyboard)
- USB gadget networking (RNDIS)
- Secure SSH access with modern OS constraints

## High-level workflow
1. Flash image to microSD
2. Enable USB gadget mode (`dwc2` + `g_ether`)
3. Confirm Windows recognizes RNDIS adapter
4. Validate IP + ARP + ping
5. Establish SSH trust and login
6. Validate services/logs

## Key lesson
“Link up” ≠ “working.” Validate each layer:
- driver presence
- IP addressing
- ARP discovery
- ICMP reachability
- SSH auth + host key trust